  "prompt": "How much did it cost Samsung to make the Galaxy S5 waterproof?",
  "response": "While Samsung has not publicly disclosed the exact cost of making the Galaxy S5 waterproof, various estimates suggest that implementing waterproofing features in smartphones can add anywhere from $5 to $20 per device to manufacturing costs. The Galaxy S5 achieved an IP67 rating, which means it can withstand immersion in water up to 1 meter for 30 minutes and is also dust-tight.\n\nThe increase in costs typically includes design alterations, additional materials for sealing components, and testing to ensure compliance with waterproofing standards. However, without specific figures released by Samsung, it's challenging to pinpoint the exact cost for the Galaxy S5.",
